<article>
    <h1>Four judges&#x2019; terms ex&#xAD;tended; nine&#xAD;teen oth&#xAD;ers reap&#xAD;pointed</h1>
    <h2>High Court Judge Quentin Loh will have his ap&#xAD;point&#xAD;ment ex&#xAD;tended by two years af&#xAD;ter his cur&#xAD;rent term ends next Thurs&#xAD;day. He will also be&#xAD;come pres&#xAD;i&#xAD;dent of the SICC with the start of his new term.</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201218/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-18"><time>2020-12-18</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Dominic Low dom&#xAD;low@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>Four High Court judges will have their terms ex­tended, while three will be reap­pointed as se­nior judges, the Supreme Court an­nounced yes­ter­day.</p>
    <p>High Court Judge Quentin Loh will have his ap­point­ment ex­tended by two years af­ter his cur­rent term ends next Thurs­day.</p>
    <p>He will also be­come pres­i­dent of the Sin­ga­pore In­ter­na­tional Com­mer­cial Court (SICC) with the start of his new term.</p>
    <p>Since his re­tire­ment in De­cem­ber 2015, Jus­tice Loh has been reap­pointed High Court judge twice and was also ap­pointed in 2018 as judge of the Supreme Court of Fiji on a part-time ba­sis for three years.</p>
    <p>The other three High Court judges – Jus­tice Chan Seng Onn, Jus­tice Lee Seiu Kin and Jus­tice Choo</p>
    <p>Han Teck – will have their ten­ure ex­tended for an­other year.</p>
    <p>Jus­tice Chan, who ac­quit­ted for­mer maid Parti Liyani of theft, will be­gin his new term on Jan 4.</p>
    <p>Jus­tice Lee, whose new ten­ure starts on Jan 30, chairs the One Ju­di­ciary Steer­ing Com­mit­tee, which over­sees and drives the im­ple­men­ta­tion of tech­nol­ogy in the courts.</p>
    <p>Jus­tice Choo, who has been pres­i­dent of the Mil­i­tary Court of Ap­peal since Novem­ber 2004, among other roles, will be­gin his new term on Feb 21.</p>
    <p>Sep­a­rately, Jus­tice Chao Hick Tin, Jus­tice An­drew Ang and Jus­tice Lai Siu Chiu will be reap­pointed as se­nior judges, with their new terms start­ing on Jan 5. Jus­tice Chao’s new ten­ure will last two years, while the other two judges will be reap­pointed for a year.</p>
    <p>Six­teen in­ter­na­tional judges will also be reap­pointed to the SICC af­ter their cur­rent terms ex­pire on Jan 4. Fif­teen will be reap­pointed for three years, while the re­main­ing judge, Jus­tice Carolyn Berger, will end her new ten­ure with the con­clu­sion of an on­go­ing case.</p>
    <p>With the new reap­point­ments, the Supreme Court will have a to­tal of 25 judges (in­clud­ing the Chief Jus­tice and four judges of ap­peal), six ju­di­cial com­mis­sion­ers, three se­nior judges and 16 in­ter­na­tional judges.</p>

